Job Description:
Data Analyst

Role Responsibilities

Responsible for building brighter financial futures by providing data to aid in business decision-making and improved efficiency in the following ways:
designs reports, spreadsheets, visualizations, dashboards and other data output, converting complex data and findings into understandable tables, charts, and written reports, as necessary;
uses data to provide output and present findings in the form of Descriptive Analytics (historic reporting), Diagnostic Analytics (problem discovery), Predictive Analytics (what will happen), and Prescriptive Analytics (what we should do);
assists in the development, maintenance, and monitoring of metrics to measure the success of Credit Union projects, products, campaigns, goals, and objectives;
makes suggestions and recommendations regarding business decisions guided by data and analysis;
protects member privacy and data security by using approved tools, systems, and secure data transfer methodologies;
collaborates with business units to identify and assess their data needs, prioritize requests, and design, build, and present appropriate output;
collaborates with the Core System team (Programmers and System Administrators) to identify, gather, validate, extract, and share data required to fulfill requests from business units and provide actionable answers to business questions;
collaborates with the Project Management team (Project Managers and Business Analysts) on projects as assigned and to discover opportunities to improve or automate inefficient processes;
assists in standardizing report, analysis, visualization, and dashboard output by documenting all work, tracking time and resource usage, developing and applying a data dictionary, following best practices, and building, maintaining, and following branding standards, such as color schemes, layouts, fonts, and other design elements;
identifies data integrity issues and assists in prioritizing and developing plans to improve data quality;
identifies and assists in prioritizing and developing plans to acquire additional tools, skillsets, and data sources;
maintains strong technical knowledge of the various systems, programs, and data techniques by reading industry publications, establishing personal networks, and attending user group meetings, educational classes, and workshops;
assists in improving the organization’s data literacy by presenting and explaining findings, demonstrating and training on the use of relevant tools, data output, and methodologies;
performs any and all other duties that may be required or needed from time to time.
Skills, Education and/or Certifications Required
Bachelor’s degree in area of finance, accounting, economics, marketing statistics/mathematics, information systems, or business management and/or demonstrated qualifying experience in financial institution branch operations, accounting, marketing, information technology, business intelligence, or similar area required.
Advanced Excel skills and proficiency Microsoft Office applications required. Knowledge of Microsoft business intelligence tools such as Management Studio (SSMS), Reporting Services (SSRS), Power BI, or Visual Studio, or the Symitar/Episys core system is a plus;
Excellent problem solving skills, as well as the ability to work without direct supervision and maintain a high degree of concentration required;
Must have good written and verbal communications skills.
